      "passageId": "P_FL07_001",
      "gateId": "FL_07_grade5_fluency",
      "module": "7.3. Grade 5 Cold Read",
      "topic": "Why Forests Need Fire",
      "genre": "informational",
      "isCold": true,
      "difficultyRank": 1,
      "targetWordCount": 200,
      "morphemeInventory": [
        "MORPH_S_tion",
        "MORPH_S_able",
        "MORPH_P_re",
        "MORPH_R_bio"
      ],
      "paragraphs": [
        {
          "sentences": [
            {
              "text": "For most of human history, people have viewed forest fires as nothing but disasters.",
              "wordList": [
                "For",
                "most",
                "of",
                "human",
                "history",
                "people",
                "have",
                "viewed",
                "forest",
                "fires",
                "as",
                "nothing",
                "but",
                "disasters"
              ]
            },
            {
              "text": "Fires destroy homes, kill animals, and fill the air with thick choking smoke.",
              "wordList": [
                "Fires",
                "destroy",
                "homes",
                "kill",
                "animals",
                "and",
                "fill",
                "the",
                "air",
                "with",
                "thick",
                "choking",
                "smoke"
              ]
            },
            {
              "text": "However, modern scientists have learned that many healthy forests actually need fire to survive over the long term.",
              "wordList": [
                "However",
                "modern",
                "scientists",
                "have",
                "learned",
                "that",
                "many",
                "healthy",
                "forests",
                "actually",
                "need",
                "fire",
                "to",
                "survive",
                "over",
                "the",
                "long",
                "term"
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "sentences": [
            {
              "text": "Small natural fires clear away dead leaves, fallen branches, and dry undergrowth that pile up over many years.",
              "wordList": [
                "Small",
                "natural",
                "fires",
                "clear",
                "away",
                "dead",
                "leaves",
                "fallen",
                "branches",
                "and",
                "dry",
                "undergrowth",
                "that",
                "pile",
                "up",
                "over",
                "many",
                "years"
              ]
            },
            {
              "text": "Without these occasional fires, that buildup grows thicker and drier each season.",
              "wordList": [
                "Without",
                "these",
                "occasional",
                "fires",
                "that",
                "buildup",
                "grows",
                "thicker",
                "and",
                "drier",
                "each",
                "season"
              ]
            },
            {
              "text": "Once it finally catches a spark, the resulting blaze burns much hotter and spreads far faster than a smaller, regular fire ever would.",
              "wordList": [
                "Once",
                "it",
                "finally",
                "catches",
                "a",
                "spark",
                "the",
                "resulting",
                "blaze",
                "burns",
                "much",
                "hotter",
                "and",
                "spreads",
                "far",
                "faster",
                "than",
                "a",
                "smaller",
                "regular",
                "fire",
                "ever",
                "would"
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "sentences": [
            {
              "text": "Certain trees actually depend on fire to reproduce.",
              "wordList": [
                "Certain",
                "trees",
                "actually",
                "depend",
                "on",
                "fire",
                "to",
                "reproduce"
              ]
            },
            {
              "text": "The cones of some pine species, including the lodgepole pine, are sealed tightly with a sticky natural resin.",
              "wordList": [
                "The",
                "cones",
                "of",
                "some",
                "pine",
                "species",
                "including",
                "the",
                "lodgepole",
                "pine",
                "are",
                "sealed",
                "tightly",
                "with",
                "a",
                "sticky",
                "natural",
                "resin"
              ]
            },
            {
              "text": "Only the intense heat of a fire can melt that resin and release the seeds onto fresh, sunlit soil where they can sprout.",
              "wordList": [
                "Only",
                "the",
                "intense",
                "heat",
                "of",
                "a",
                "fire",
                "can",
                "melt",
                "that",
                "resin",
                "and",
                "release",
                "the",
                "seeds",
                "onto",
                "fresh",
                "sunlit",
                "soil",
                "where",
                "they",
                "can",
                "sprout"
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "sentences": [
            {
              "text": "Today, careful forest managers sometimes set planned, controlled burns to imitate this natural cycle.",
              "wordList": [
                "Today",
                "careful",
                "forest",
                "managers",
                "sometimes",
                "set",
                "planned",
                "controlled",
                "burns",
                "to",
                "imitate",
                "this",
                "natural",
                "cycle"
              ]
            },
            {
              "text": "These small managed fires reduce the dangerous fuel buildup, recycle nutrients back into the soil, and open clearings where new young plants can take root.",
              "wordList": [
                "These",
                "small",
                "managed",
                "fires",
                "reduce",
                "the",
                "dangerous",
                "fuel",
                "buildup",
                "recycle",
                "nutrients",
                "back",
                "into",
                "the",
                "soil",
                "and",
                "open",
                "clearings",
                "where",
                "new",
                "young",
                "plants",
                "can",
                "take",
                "root"
              ]
            },
            {
              "text": "What once looked like pure destruction is, in many forests, a powerful part of renewal.",
              "wordList": [
                "What",
                "once",
                "looked",
                "like",
                "pure",
                "destruction",
                "is",
                "in",
                "many",
                "forests",
                "a",
                "powerful",
                "part",
                "of",
                "renewal"
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
